&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directorate of Emergency and Acute Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locum Consultant in Acute Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting to Locum Consultant posts in Acute Medicine to Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust based at the Northern General Hospital. There are 1.5 WTE available and therefore applications would be considered from both whole time and applicants wishing to work less than full time. The posts are to start as soon as possible for a fixed term period of 12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must be registered with the GMC with a valid licence to practice. For further information please visit the GMC website and click on the Registration and Licensing link. You will also have completed Specialist Training (or equivalent) and ideally be entered on the Specialist Register of the GMC, or have a CCT date within six months of the date of interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should any further vacancies arise, shortlisted candidates will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research is encouraged and full facilities are available. Applications from those unable, for personal reasons, to work on a whole time basis or a job share basis will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Non-UK/EEA applicants should ensure they are aware of the recent changes to the Immigration rules. For further information on how this may affect your application visit the UK Government website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants experiencing problems applying, please contact Medical HR Department, (0114) 271 2968 quoting reference 190-STH-20-222&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust promotes Equality of opportunity and Diversity within the workplace.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Claire Gardner, Clinical Lead, Email address: claire.gardner14@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Ben Cooper, Clinical Director, email addres: brcooper@nhs.net or Mr C Powell-Wiffen, Operations Director, email address: Chris.Powell-Wiffen1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
